newsitem.title: USA: Fannie Mae to redeem $200 mln in notes.
newsitem.headline: Fannie Mae to redeem $200 mln in notes.

text.p: Fannie Mae Friday said that on June 18 it will redeem all outstanding amounts of three medium-term note issues totalling $200 million, as follows.
The notes were originally set to mature June 18, 2001. The redemption price of the notes will be 100 percent of the principal amount plus interest accrued to the redemption date, Fannie Mae said.
